              <tr><td colspan="3"><hr width="100%" size="1"></td></tr>
              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Description</b><br>
These wintery peaks be the front yard o' the hale and hearty Barbarians, the Wolves o' the North, the mightiest that Norrath has offered up. There be no rain here in the Everfrost, as I hear the humans whine about, and the peaks glisten with snow at all times. This makes it easy to navigate even at night, despite our lack of the fancy sight that me grandfather Turbin the Sojourner tells me them shorter and/or stupider races have...
<br><br>
Our pups grow into such mighty heroes because they learn their craft in the best training area in all the land. Young bears, wolves, and spiders wander about begging to become the hats and clothing of our rambunctious adolescents, and many a Gnoll and Goblin youngin has had their lunch money
stolen and their ancestry called into question by our precious little ones. The brave can hunt here well into their 7th season, should they desire, and for the even braver still, three cursed, angry, and dead bards wander about, to be vanquished well past 10th. These are the mightier cousins to the weak and decrepit decaying skeletons that are so numerous in our peaks we wonder
if a Necromancer lives beneath the ice, raising them up again and again.  
<br><br>
Our precious little ones earn a spectacular allowance for all their cleaning up of this yard trash, and many a Barbarian has a mighty chest full o' gold upon reaching their maturity. Our rambunctious heroes in their 7th season tend to seek out greater glory in the wide, vast plains of the frozen
tundra. Adult Polar Bears and Spiders, Goblin Scouts, Snow Kitties, huge and glorious Mammoths and their babes, and the vile and vicious Snow Orcs all eke out an existence in these rolling plains. That is, until Halas cries Have at thee! and releases their bravest! The veterans of Halas wag their beards and shake their heads in amusement of the shouting cheers heard so
often across the plains. Groups taking on young Mammoths, or the grunting, hulking Orc Troopers, Mountaineers, then the Orcish Shaman. We warn those under their 10th season to be wary of the latter two, as they be worthy adversaries indeed. And lastly, terrible Ice Boned Skeletons, enchanted such
as they are, they cannot be hit without a weapon equally as enchanted.  The mighty of Halas make a decent wage and can improve their skills well into their 20th season, should they desire to keep to the hunt here in the tundra, and for even meatier game for the greatest of warriors, shaman, and scampy rogues, venture across the frozen river to the home of the Icy Orcs, or the lair of the stinking Ice Goblins who can't even keep their kit on when they die.  And, of course, the dragon...
<br><br>
The Tundra is a mystical land, being so close as it is to the lair of an ancient mighty scaly beastie known as Vox. As such, many a quest for money and magic can be begun, or finished, in this arctic paradise.  Ancient caves beneath the ice offer up their secrets to only those brave enough to take a dip in the frozen river, and many have perished who did not seek the help of our arcane Shaman. Many more wander aimlessly through the Peaks, too foolish to ask for aid from a passing Barbarian. The weak cannot hope to survive long, and for those without a decent guide or good map, the city of Halas remains a hidden mystery never to be reached.
<br><br>
And that is for the best, for the citizens of Halas are not kind to strangers, and as there are no creatures they cannot vanquish, don't expect to be able to impress them with the killing of their enemies. The only way
to endear yourself to the mighty Barbarians is to do their bidding, and prove yourself worthy by completing the quests they send you on, into the heart of the Everfrost Peaks.
<br><br>
Oh, and a request from my father's friend's sister's boyfriend, Karg: he asks that you kindly stop killing him, please. He's only a simple tailor trying to make an honest wage...
<br><br>
Boomshaka Laka
<br>
Mighty Wolf-dam of the North!<br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:10, showing:1-5) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=zone&tid=28')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:cynner13@yahoo.com">Fenira - Barbarian Shaman</a> of the E'Ci server on Apr. 14, 2000 at 05:57am said...<br>
Re: Glacier Bear; found him this morning and soloed him at lvl 31.  I stood on the ice above the cave and used Sense Animal; you know, that useless spell :) He picked up right off.  Had to use it again once I was in the cave, but he was walking just down the hall from the entrance.  He still conned blue to me, and I ended the fight with no mana and 2 bubs of health. Went in fully buffed, and hit him with the bugs (he resisted the first time) and layered Dots.  The new DOT wear off messages helped alot here, so I knew when to recast.  He was tough, hitting for an average of 40-50 when he wasn't doing 1-5. I only had to greater heal once.  He dropped the Glacier Bear pelt and the Icon of the Devout which I think is for a wizard quest.  As well as a high quality bear pelt, a ruined bear pelt and some meat, which I made into a sandwich and ate, and I'll sew the pelts into something nice.  You shouldn't waste anything you know.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:cynner13@yahoo.com">Fenira Jormungundr</a> of the E'Ci server on Apr. 07, 2000 at 08:00am said...<br>
More information on Mr. Glacier Bear would definately be appreciated.  Spawn rate and location number.  Found the caves just fine, and killed wandering skeletons.  But decided to vacate when the Lich started running around.  As a note; the Lich can not see through Rogue Hide, my brother Pdwyr, walked right over him at 30th level while hiding/sneaking.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:steve@bezier.com">Zulu Suntoucher</a> of the Luclin server on Apr. 04, 2000 at 06:55pm said...<br>
Just two comments. IMHO, Everfrost is hands down the best zone up to level 6 or so. Great money to be made from quests, and unlike most newbie zones, it has plenty of 3rd level mobs or so. Also, the description of the zone is the BEST I have ever read. In character, vivid, fun to read, and has lots of info that is actually useful, as well as colorful. Kudos to Boomshaka. :)<br><br>
<a href="mailto:hangin@cvzoom.net">Allanocus</a> of the Innoruuk server on Mar. 20, 2000 at 01:25pm said...<br>
The message about the 3 different higher level skeletons is for a girl in a bar that lost her brother. <br><br>
